  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Inability to distribute medicines to hospitals",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Government Pharmacists Society said that the drugs given to Sri Lanka to address the shortage of drugs are not being distributed to the hospitals; reported.",
        "The Government Pharmacists Society said that the shortage of medicines has reduced to some extent due to the supply of medicines provided by various parties, but due to the fuel crisis, it is not possible to distribute these medicines to the hospitals.",
        "Ajith Thilakaratna, President of the Government Pharmacists' Association, said that the medical distribution department of the Ministry of Health did not have enough medicines and medical supplies before the last few weeks, but due to donations from various parties, this shortage has been partially resolved.",
        "He mentioned that although medicines and medical supplies are available in the medical supply department, they are not available in the hospitals.",
        "In the current situation, hospitals are not in a position to send vehicles to the medical supply unit in Colombo, and lack of fuel has also affected the vehicles of the medical supply unit, he said.",
        "Ajith Thilakaratna, President of Government Pharmacists Association said that not only one hospital has been affected, many hospitals have also been affected, especially those in remote areas."
      ],
